.eu/eurostat/tgm/refreshTableAction.do?tab=table&plugin=1&pcode=tec00001&language=en |title = Eurostat - Tables, Graphs and Maps Interface (TGM) table}}</ref>\n| \u20ac28.037&nbsp;billion\n| \u20ac30.476&nbsp;billion\n| \u20ac48.339&nbsp;billion\n| \u20ac106.852&nbsp;billion\n|-\n! GDP (nominal) per capita (2019)<ref name=\"ec.europa.eu\"/>\n| \u20ac21,200\n| \u20ac15,900\n| \u20ac17,300\n| \u20ac17,700\n|-\n! [[Military budget]] (2018)\n| \u20ac533&nbsp;million<sup>(\u20ac523mil.+additional \u20ac10mil.)</sup><ref>{{cite web\n| url = http://www.kaitseministeerium.ee/en/objectives-activities/defence-budget\n| title = Defence budget \u2013 Kaitseministeerium\n| website = kaitseministeerium.ee\n}}</ref>\n| \u20ac576&nbsp;million<ref>{{cite web\n| url = http://www.janes.com/article/75972/latvia-s-defence-spending-to-reach-2-of-gdp-in-2018\n| title = Latvia's defence spending to reach 2% of GDP in 2018 \u2013 Jane's 360\n| website = janes.com\n}}</ref>\n| \u20ac891&nbsp;million<sup>(\u20ac873mil.+additional \u20ac18mil.)</sup><ref>{{cite web\n| url = https://www.vz.lt/verslo-aplinka/2018/07/10/lietuva-turbut-dar-siemet-didins-gynybos-biudzeta\n| title = Lietuva turb\u016bt dar \u0161iemet didins gynybos biud\u017eet\u0105\n| last = Bns\n}}</ref>\n| \u20ac2.0&nbsp;billion\n|-\n! [[Gini coefficient|Gini Index]] (2015)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dataworldbank.org/indicator/SI.POV.GINI?end=2015&locations=EE&start=2015&view=map&year=2015|title=GINI index (World Bank estimate) {{! }} Data|publisher=World Bank|access-date=28 May 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180422062944/https://data.worldbank.org/indicator/SI.POV.GINI?end=2015&locations=EE&start=2015&view=map&year=2015|archive-date=22 April 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n| 32.7\n| 34.2\n| 37.4\n| {{NA}}\n|-\n! [[Human Development Index|HDI]] (2019)<ref>{{Cite web\n |url = http://hdr.undp.org/en/2019-update\n |title = &#124; Human Development Reports\n |access-date = 14 September 2018\n |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180914203906/http://hdr.undp.org/en/2018-update\n |archive-date = 14 September 2018\n |url-status = dead\n |df = dmy-all\n}}</ref>\n| 0.882 ([[Developed country|Very High]])\n| 0.854 ([[Developed country|Very High]])\n| 0.869 ([[Developed country|Very High]])\n| {{NA}}\n|-\n! Internet [[Country code top-level domain|TLD]]\n| [[.ee]]\n| [[.lv]]\n| [[.lt]]\n| {{NA}}\n|-\n! [[List of country calling codes|Calling code]]\n| [[+372]]\n| [[+371]]\n| [[+370]]\n| {{NA}}\n|}\n\n===Cities===\n{{Largest cities\n| name = Largest cities of the Baltic states <!-- name of the template, e.g. Largest cities of Chile -->\n| class = nav <!-- can be changed to \"nav\" to alter the template's colour scheme -->\n| country = Baltic states <!-- the name of the country, e.g. Chile -->\n| kind = cities <!-- replace \"cities and towns\" in the title w/ anything, e.g. \"conurbations\" -->\n| stat_ref = [[Statistics Estonia]], Statistics Latvia and [[Statistics Lithuania]] estimates for 2019. <!-- source of the pop. figures, e.g. Instituto Nacional de Estadisticas de Chile or use {{URL| }} -->\n| list_by_pop = List of cities in the Baltic States by population <!-- link to the list of cities in the given country, if possible sorted by population -->\n| div_name = Country <!-- the name of the main administrative subdivision, e.g. Province, State, Region... -->\n| div_link = Country <!-- the template will automatically create a link for \"div_name of country\" (e.g. Provinces of Chile), if this doesn't work you can use this field -->\n| city_1 = Riga <!-- a link to the article about the largest city -->\n| div_1 = Latvia <!-- link to the administrative subdivision where said city is located -->\n| pop_1 = 632,614 <!-- population, do include the commas to separate the thousands -->\n| img_1 = Riga Skyline Panorama, Latvia - Diliff.jpg <!-- a picture showing an overview of the city -->\n| city_2 = Vilnius | div_2 = Lithuania | pop_2 = 557,440 | img_2 = Vilnius Modern Skyline At 